description.plain:
Water Me Down is the only song on Vagabon that Tamko didn’t write and produce entirely by herself. The original beat was first written by Eric Littman and the vocals / lyrics were provided by Tamko. The lyrics were inspired by a frustrating phone call with her boyfriend. After the conversation she wrote down all the things she wished she’d said to him.

After the vocals had been tracked Tamko took control of the production to finish the song, with Eric providing some additional collaboration.

songs.title: Water Me Down (Pamcy Remix)

annotations:
In this relationship the author felt that they were being “watered down” by the other person.

In an interview on the Song Exploder podcast she said the following:

“Water me down” it means to be diluted, like someone taking away from the pure concentration of a person. And so, the way that I’m using it in this song is, this really dilutes everything that is good about me.
